A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Health Care Facilities – Hospitals and Freestanding Birthing Centers –
3 Perinatal Care Standards
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Maryland Department of Health to adopt regulations
5 establishing minimum perinatal care standards for certain hospitals that meet or
6 exceed the Maryland Perinatal System Standards; requiring certain hospitals and
7 freestanding birthing centers, as a condition of licensure, to comply with certain
8 minimum perinatal care standards; and generally relating to standards of care for
9 hospitals and freestanding birthing centers.
